Hi Viktor
Hope all is well; I noticed your background as a developer for FX rates within an e-trading environment and wanted to reach out to you.

I’m looking for an individual with your skillset for a top ten North American bank located in New York City. 
Are you available for a chat? 

Kind Regards,
Edgar

Delivery Consultant

Hello, Viktor - 

My name’s Shannon. I'm placing Software Engineers for new roles in NYC and thought you'd be a great fit. These are all full-time positions with benefits. (Remote OK)

Do you have time for online interviews this week or next?

Use my link https://hi.uptownhire.com/oq1 to sign up. Once you receive an interview request you'll see all job details including salary and total compensation to help you confidently move forward with the interview.

You might receive interview requests from other employers as well; just approve or decline the interview requests as you see fit.

Will you let me know either way? Thank you!

Shannon Smith
Technical Recruiter
how are you 2

Hi Viktor,

I am working with an electronic trading company based in Greenwich, CT who are looking to hire an experienced Engineer.

They're looking for a candidate who is extremely proficient in JavaScript, Typescript and Node.JS

The role is mostly remote - they're looking for you to be onsite in Greenwich 1-2 days every two weeks.

They're targeting up to $200,000 + 20-30% bonus potential.

Let me know if you're interested in learning more about this, and what time we can speak further on it tomorrow,

Best,

Will

William Leslie
Senior Vice President - DevOps, SRE and Cloud Engineering

Hi Viktor,

I have multiple AVP to MD level opportunities with a Canadian Multinational Financial Institute based in either their New York or Toronto office with a focus on Electronic Trading Systems in Front Office.

Key Skills of interest are:

Knowledge of C++, Core Java or C#
Experience with trading engines across multiple asset classes
Previous low-latency development experience
Front office experience 
 
Should you possess any of the above skill sets and are open to discussing further, please let me know.

Alternatively, should you believe this role would be a better fit for a friend or colleague I would appreciate the introduction to assist them accordingly.

Thank you

Jermaine Flanders
Banking Delivery Lead | Banking | High Performance, Low Latency | Trading Systems | C# | C++ | Core Java

Viktor

I am keen to speak with you on behalf of an industry leading energy trading & investment firm based in Stamford, CT.

They are keen to find experienced developers either already based in the area, or willing to relocate with financial backing and support from the company. They are able to offer hybrid working arrangements and flexible hours.

**This role is for full-time hires only, unfortunately no C2C**
* This client is able to sponsor H1B if required***

They are keen to hire multiple developers across different levels of seniority - ideally those individuals will possess strong java experienced on the back end.

Experienced Developers - $100,000 - $130,000 basic + bonus

Senior Developers - $135,000 - $150,000 basic + bonus

Lead Developers - $155,000 - $180,000 basic + bonus

No prior energy industry experience is required, although would be an advantage.

If this sounds like something you may be interested, can we please have a short call to discuss? What number can I reach you on?

Many thanks,
Farhan

Farhan Janjua
Senior Associate - Technology and Innovation at HC Group
Understood! thanks for the response, happy to keep in touch!
